<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1166,1478]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1239,1263]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">Notes.</emphasis>
The hemielytral pattern in this species exhibits yellow markings similar to those in 
<taxonomicName authority="Nieser &amp; Chen, 1992" authorityName="Nieser &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Ochteridae" genus="Ochterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentatus">
<emphasis box="[1267,1436,1238,1262]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">
<collectingCountry box="[1267,1290,1239,1262]" name="Iceland" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">O</collectingCountry>
. unidentatus
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[151,391,1274,1298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Chen, P. (1992) Notes on Gelastocoridae and Ochteridae (Heteroptera) with the description of five new species. Storkia, 1, 2 - 13." type="journal article" year="1992">
Nieser &amp; Chen, 
<number box="[332,391,1274,1298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the body form is less elongated. The lateral expansions of the pronotum are wider than in 
<emphasis box="[151,326,1310,1334]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicName box="[151,321,1310,1334]" class="Insecta" family="Ochteridae" genus="Ochterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentatus">
<collectingCountry box="[151,174,1311,1334]" name="Iceland" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">O</collectingCountry>
. unidentatus
</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and the brown colour on the posterior margin of the pronotum is more dispersed. The anterior femura are not at all curved in the apical part. The frontal plate is dark with yellow metallic reflections, and there are more carinated ridge markings on the margins near the eyes and in the centre of the inferior part than in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ochteridae" genus="Ochterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">
<collectingCountry box="[1409,1432,1383,1406]" name="Iceland" pageId="3" pageNumber="65">O</collectingCountry>
. unidentatus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This latter characteristic was not noted by previous authors except 
<bibRefCitation author="Kormilev" box="[1102,1299,1418,1442]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" refString="Kormilev, N. A. (1971) Ochteridae from the Oriental and Australian regions (Hemiptera-Heteroptera). Pacific Insects, 13 (3 - 4), 429 - 444." type="journal article" year="1971">
Kormilev (
<number box="[1230,1290,1418,1442]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and is not reported in Schell’s revision, nor by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[559,811,1454,1478]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Chen, P. (1992) Notes on Gelastocoridae and Ochteridae (Heteroptera) with the description of five new species. Storkia, 1, 2 - 13." type="journal article" year="1992">
Nieser &amp; Chen (
<number box="[742,803,1454,1478]" pageId="3" pageNumber="65" value="1992.0">1992</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
